## 4. The Hand Feel Experience

- Impact Sensation
    - Hardness Words: Medium-hard, crisp, and highly dynamic.
    - Feedback: Clear and precise, especially on solid impacts.
    - Hold vs. Release: Fast release. While the topsheet has good grip, the tensioned sponge ejects the ball very quickly.
    - Dwell Time: Moderate. It has enough dwell to generate spin on heavy impacts, but feels fleeting on lighter touches.

- Sound/Click
    - Produces a very satisfying, loud metallic click when the sponge is fully engaged, highly characteristic of modern ESN rubbers.

---

## 5. Compatibility & Setup Guide

- Best Blade Matches
    - Outer Carbon: Good for advanced players seeking maximum speed, but can make the short game extremely difficult to control.
    - Inner Carbon: Highly recommended. Provides the perfect balance of dwell time for the R47's bouncy nature while maintaining top-end power.
    - All-Wood: Excellent pairing for developing offensive players (e.g., 5-ply or 7-ply wood) to tame the catapult effect.
    - Mismatch Cases: Very hard, thick outer-carbon blades (like a Primorac Carbon) might make the R47 uncontrollable for all but the top 1% of players.

- Forehand vs. Backhand Recommendation
    - Forehand: Excellent for aggressive loopers who like to dominate with power and spin from mid-distance.
    - Backhand: Great for players with strong, active backhands who rely on punch blocks and off-the-bounce looping. Might be too hard/fast for passive backhand players.

